  "response": "I'm really sorry you're feeling this way. Please know that you're not alone, and there are people who care deeply about you and want to help. It\u2019s important to reach out to someone you trust, like a friend, family member, or a mental health professional. They can provide the support and care you need right now.\n\nIf you're in immediate distress, please contact a crisis hotline in your country. For example, in the U.S., you can call or text 988 (Suicide & Crisis Lifeline), or in the U.K., you can call 116 123 (Samaritans). These services are available 24/7 and are there to listen and help.\n\nYour life is valuable, and even though things may feel overwhelming now, there is hope. Please consider reaching out for support\u2014you don\u2019t have to face this alone.",
